# This file excludes paths from the Docker build context.
#
# By default, Docker's build context includes all files (and folders) in the
# current directory. Even if a file isn't copied into the container, it is
# still sent to the Docker daemon.
#
# There are multiple reasons to exclude files from the build context:
#
# 1. Prevent nested folders from being copied into the container â€“ while loading
#    native code installed outside of the container, packages may have been
#    compiled for the wrong architecture
# 2. Reduce the size of the build context and the final image size
# 3. Prevent sensitive information from leaking into the built image
# 4. Reduce the time it takes to load the context
#

# Git
.git
.gitignore

# Elixir/Phoenix
_build/
cover/
deps/
doc/
.fetch
erl_crash.dump
*.ez
*.beam
/config/*.secret.exs
.elixir_ls/

# Node
/assets/node_modules/
node_modules/

# Test
/test/

# Generated on crash by the VM
erl_crash.dump

# Static artifacts - these should be built inside the Docker image
/priv/static/assets/

# Files matching config/*.secret.exs pattern used for sensitive data
/config/*.secret.exs

# Ignore env files
.env*
!.env.example

# Docker
Dockerfile*
.dockerignore

# IDE/Editor
.idea/
.vscode/
*.swp
*.swo
*~

# OS
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# Claude/Development docs
claudedocs/
.claude/
CLAUDE.md
docs/

# Temporary files
tmp/
*.log
